# bad-keyword.tflw — CHECK-ONLY FIXTURE (PLAN M1.5): a typo'd step keyword, deliberately invalid
# syntax that never parses — demonstrates `tflw check`'s teaching diagnostic (TF011: unrecognised
# statement keyword, "did you mean `expect`?").
#
# This file (and the rest of tests/.checkonly/) is invalid .tflw and would break a bare `tflw
# run`/`tflw check` if it lived anywhere non-dot — `tflw check` shares the exact same
# discovery/validation path as `tflw run` (both skip dot-prefixed entries). Demonstrate it with an
# explicit file argument only:
#   npx tflw check tests/.checkonly/bad-keyword.tflw

test "a typo'd step keyword"
  api GET /health
  expct status equals 200
